cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the synthesis of blood vessel geometries in medical images. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the parametrization of blood vessel geometries, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of GANs for synthesizing blood vessel geometries could also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
